"The Czech administration of social security will no longer request an extract from the commercial register when carrying out a check on the taxes of the insured person," said ČSSZ spokesman Jana Buraňová.
The aim of the Absurdity survey of the year is to consult the rules and regulations that businesses and entrepreneurs in Czech Republic must respect and try to eliminate those who are absurd.
This year forms for the fourth time part of the corporate tournament of the publication Hospodářské noviny and begins to create a hobby also among the general public.
While last year's edition was attended by three thousand voters, this year nearly reached four thousand.
And it's not surprising, since we still have a number of legal obligations that must be respected simply to trade.
"Perhaps in number of papers necessary for tax reporting we are in the first place worldwide," says Karel Havlíček of the Association of Small and Medium-sized Enterprises and Entrepreneurs of the Czech Republic.
