"This is generating divisions within families."
During the rule of the Khmer Rouge in Cambodia between 1975 and 1979, approximately 1.7 million people were executed or died of hunger, illness or overwork.
When the Vietnamese invaded and overthrown the government led by Pol Pot in 1979, the remains of the regime and its military fled to the Cambodian border with Thailand.
